        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.foundationdb.org/alexmiller/{size}/326_2.png",
        "created_at": "2019-06-03T20:22:57.459Z",
        "cooked": "<p>\u2026 man, we really need to go clean up and rewrite most of the docs surrounding recommended configuration and performance numbers.</p>\n<p>It really depends on your storage characteristics.  For running on physical SSDs, which isn\u2019t the network attached storage that Kubernetes deployments sometimes have, we\u2019ve typically seen something around 1:8 for <code>ssd</code> and 1:2 for <code>memory</code> being near optimal.  Running a write benchmark and seeing if it improves if you add more logs is the easy and accurate way to find your optimal ratio.</p>",
